<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-83-0436 </DOCNO><TEXT>A key policy proposal in the current debate over the control of acid rainand other pollutants is permitting companies to buy, sell, or lease emissionsrights or &quot;credits.&quot; This book is a study of the theoretical and practicaldifficulties involved in the creation of a national emissions tradingprogram, a survey of the positions of the utilities and public regulatorycommissions toward such a program, and estimates of the potential environmentaland economic impact of emissions trading. The authors demonstrate theadvantages of controlling acid rain through a market approach ratherthan through a regulatory approach.</TEXT></DOC>